    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-07T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-07T07:00:00-05:00" n="197"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860h.00/7–745: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 197 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in <persName corresp="#p_Y1">Yugoslavia</persName>
                    </hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SH2" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shantz</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d197fn1">The gist of this message was included in telegram
                        No. 11 of July 10 from <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">Grew</persName> to
                            <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName> (file No. 740.00119
                        Potsdam/7–1045).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]<note n="2" xml:id="d197fn2">For the full text
                            of this message, see <ref target="#d553">document No. 553</ref>.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Belgrade</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-07T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 7, 1945—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>247. …</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SI1">Šubašić</persName> expressed hope that Big Three
                    meeting will make a public reference to this<note n="3" xml:id="d197fn3">See
                            <ref target="#d553">document No. 553</ref>.</note> and remind Yugo Govt
                    that [<persName corresp="#p_TMJB1">Tito</persName>-<persName corresp="#p_SI1"
                        >Šubašić</persName>] agreement<note n="4" xml:id="d197fn4">See <ref
                            target="frus1945Malta#pg_251">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, The Conferences at Malta and
                            Yalta, 1945, pp. 251</ref>–<ref target="frus1945Malta#pg_254"
                        >254</ref>.</note> must be carried out. …</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SRCS1">Stevenson</persName> and I believe such action
                    desirable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SH2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shantz</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
